      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, please don't apologize. It took real courage to share this, and I'm glad you did.\n\nWhat you're describing — stopping runs halfway because of foot pain, and noticing it getting worse — is important information, and it matters that you've told me now. The fact that you kept showing up, even while dealing with something this uncomfortable, says a lot about your commitment. That's not something to be embarrassed about. It's actually something worth acknowledging.\n\nI do need to be straightforward with you here though: diagnosing what's happening in your foot and telling you how to treat it is genuinely outside what I'm able to do as a coach. I don't want to guess at something that could affect your long-term health if I get it wrong. Plantar fasciitis that's been trained through can take a few different forms, and some of them need specific clinical assessment — imaging, hands-on evaluation, the kind of things a physiotherapist or sports medicine doctor can actually do properly.\n\n**What I'd really encourage you to do is go back to your physio as soon as you can** — ideally this week. Let them know exactly what you've told me: that the pain has been worsening over recent weeks and that you've had to cut runs short. That context is going to help them assess where things stand.\n\nIn the meantime, on the training side — which *is* my lane — I'd suggest pausing the running completely until you've had that appointment. Not as a punishment, but because your foot is trying to tell you something, and continuing to load it before knowing what's going on could make the path back longer, not shorter. Rest right now is genuinely an investment in getting back to running well.\n\nOnce you have clearance and a clear picture from your physio, I'll be right here to rebuild a plan with you — carefully, at whatever pace makes sense.\n\nWhat does your access to your physio look like? Can you get in to see them soon?"
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_011bPWsmucCUfk3Be95v1wgb"
    }
  ],
